      <abstract encodinganalog="description">The Edward LaChapelle avalanche control video collection (1950-1970) consists of films about avalanche danger, control and research at Utah ski areas and around the world.  The collection also includes some of LaChapelle's home movies and other ski related footage.  Edward LaChapelle was an American glaciologist, mountaineer, skier, author, and professor and a pioneer in Avalanche research, safety and forecasting.</abstract>
